The paper discusses a specific problem related to information retrieval in a database, which is a common topic in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of Boolean statements and the retrieval of items from a specific source also suggest a connection to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the importance of team work, which could be related to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of search strategies and the focus on accuracy could be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
